---
title: One-Pan Banh-Mi-Style Turkey Tacos with Pickled Cucumber and Sriracha Mayo
description: Combining tender meat, crunchy pickled veggies, fresh cilantro, spicy chiles, and creamy spreads, the Vietnamese banh mi is one of our all-time favorite sandwiches. Here, we take all those same flavors and textures and channel them into some seriously delicious tacos. Tangy-sweet beef is piled into warm tortillas with sautéed carrots, pickled cucumber, cilantro, and Sriracha mayo. Taco ’bout an epic dinner!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6655edcf8a4eed4f27b52eef-bacd9d7e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6657719c66fcbf26f0fd977f-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1970 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-banh-mi-style-turkey-tacos-6657719c66fcbf26f0fd977f
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve @lime{1}. Trim and halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into
half-moons. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, juice from half the lime, 
@?sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Stir in cucumber. Set aside to quick-pickle.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce} and cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{1%minute}.
Season with salt and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce};
season with a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned
and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp} and remaining vinegar. Bring to a simmer, then immediately
turn off heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with @sriracha{1%tsp} to taste.
Season with salt. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with saucy beef, carrots, pickled cucumber (draining first),
and cilantro. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo. Cut remaining lime into wedges and serve on the side.

> You can swap in chicken or turkey for beef. No need to break up chicken into pieces!